Preheat oven to 475 degrees F. Season tomatoes, if desired, with Kosher salt, then drizzle with 1 tsp. Bertolli(R) Extra Virgin Olive Oil. Arrange in baking pan and roast 15 minutes or until wilted. Chop tomatoes and set aside. Saute pancetta with 1 Tbsp. Bertolli(R) Extra Light(TM) Tasting Olive Oil over medium-high heat until crisp. Add garlic and cook 30 seconds. Add mushrooms, roasted tomatoes and 1 cup broth. Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce heat to low and simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes. Add cooked fettuccine to mushroom mixture, then add remaining broth, parsley and mint. Simmer 5 minutes. Serve, if desired, with parmesan cheese and drizzle with remaining 1 Tbsp. Bertolli Extra Virgin Olive Oil.